<HEADLINE>
CUP DOES NOT A PRO LEAGUE MAKE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Awesome baby, this Summer of Hamm.
</P>
<P>
   By next week, we'll have the Foudy Flakes cereal, the
Shake-n-Akers Chicken drive-thru, the ``Cha-Cha'' Chastain
whips-and-chains Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Let's leave it at that.
</P>
<P>
   Chick kickball might never be more exciting than it will be this
week leading up to the prom at Pasadena on Saturday. It's more than
just soccer moms loading the SUV full of pig-tailed girls looking
for role models. It's also giving the sports-hog dads something to
help them bond with their daughters for a change. For that, we
thank you.
</P>
<P>
   But please, to the organizers, when you see 92,542 at the Rose
Bowl this weekend, don't get some crazy ideas of milking this into
some kind of nobody-cares women's pro league. Allow this to shine
for what it is _ a national event of character, camaraderie and
pure fun. Don't dilute it for the love of money.
</P>
<P>
   __ Bring Charles Oakley out this way and the Lakers might be
able to wrangle him an endorsement deal with a certain sunglasses
company. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Ross Porter stat of the week: 19 times this year, the Dodgers
have had a double to lead off an inning only to strand the runner.
. . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Throwing Raul Mondesi into the leadoff spot isn't as much an
act of desperation as activating reliever Antonio Osuna will be. .
. .
</P>
<P>
   __ What current Dodger or Angel can complain if he's left off
the All-Star teams named this week?. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ The pen, the pen, the bullpen's on fire. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Chin-Feng Chen update: The made-in-Taiwan 21-year-old
outfielder on the Dodgers Single-A San Bernardino team is one of
nine position players listed in the latest Baseball America as a
Minor League Player of the Year candidate. In 74 games: .297, 16
HRs, 68 RBI, 14 doubles, six triples. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ If the Mets quit on master of disguise Bobby Valentine,
rumors are that Kevin Kennedy will be there to step in. Just like a
few years back when Kennedy replaced Valentine in Texas. And the
rumors will then start of Valentine replacing Davey Johnson. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Kevin Costner's new baseball flick, ``For the Love of the
Game,'' has a Sept. 17 release date. Vin Scully and Steve Lyons
have roles as broadcasters in it, where scenes of Yankee Stadium
were recreated at the Warner Brother studios in Burbank. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Andre Agassi could have a profound effect on the divorce rate
after this French-Wimbledon run. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Don't go, Steffi. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ With her $154,700 prize money, Alexandra Stevenson said she
wants to buy herself a Volvo convertible and then get her mom a new
washer and dryer. Y'know, once her nutty mom gets around to selling
her own book rights to her fatal-distraction life with Dr. J, it'll
be like laundering money. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ And no one has stepped up to claim Wilt Chamberlain as his or
her father yet? . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Coming soon to Irvine is the Ken Norton Restaurant and
Nightclub that'll feature a vodka and citrus juice smoothie called
the ``Knockout Punch.'' . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ A Tiger Woods kids clinic won't be complete until he teaches
each one how to juggle a Top Flite on the face of his or her wedge
and then whack the bejesus out of it. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Happened to spot esteemed sportscaster Tom Kelly cruisin'
down Sunset the other day in a pretty nice E320 gold Mercedes.
Which also had a gold license plate frame. Which read: ``My other
toy has (a slang word for breasts).'' Classy. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
