<DOCNO> NYT19990704.0127 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-04 22:10 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9184 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-FEATURE-SPI &LR;      07-04 0147
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-FEATURE-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Monday, July 5, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Larry Johnson on the Post-Intelligencer's National/Foreign
Desk at (206) 448-8035.
</P>
<P>
   VECSEY-COLUMN (PALO ALTO) _ It's official now, which should make
FIFA, U.S. Soccer, ESPN, Nike, adidas, little girls, big boys,
women and soccer fans across the 50 United States extremely happy:
They can do no wrong. The U.S. Women's World Cup team can show up
for huge games like Sunday's semifinal with dead legs and overall
psychic fatigue and still hold up their end of the bargain.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS _ Seattle Mariners play at Texas.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
