   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- July 4, 1999 -- ENGLANDER-INTERVIEW, 7-4 --
Nathan Englander, 29, who has won praise for his first book, ``For
the Relief of Unbearable Urges,'' a story collection. The book,
published by Alfred A. Knopf, is a collection of nine stories about
Orthodox Jews in extreme circumstances _ in the Soviet Union,
Israel and Brooklyn. The characters face and sometimes overcome
spiritual, moral and sexual crises. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
